SA has 276,242 confirmed cases of Covid-19 and 4,079 deaths. This in an increase of 12,058 infections and 108 fatalities from figures released on Saturday night. This was announced by President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday evening as he addressed the nation. “A quarter of those who have died, passed away in the last week,” he said. Ramaphosa described Covid-19 as the “gravest crisis in the history of our democracy”. “The surge in infections ... has now arrived. The storm is upon us. More than a quarter of a million South Africans have been infected by the coronavirus, and we know many more infections have gone undetected,” the president said. On Saturday, SA moved into the global top 10 in terms of confirmed infections. This is a developing story.